  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Decision rationale relies on the presence of a validated hemolysis fault-detection criterion (RH < 1) as the primary — and treated as sufficient — basis for accepting the model for the COU safety goal.",
